Package gov.nasa.pds.objectAccess.table

Implementations of access objects and interfaces for reading and writing tables and table fields.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FieldAdapter
    Defines an adapter object for table fields that can read the field value from a byte array or write the field value into a byte array.
    TableAdapter
    Defines a facade object that gives access to a table, either binary fixed, character fixed, or delimited.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BitFieldAdapter
    Implements a field adapter for binary bit fields.
    DefaultFieldAdapter
    Implements an adapter object for table fields that can read the field value from a byte array or write the field value into a byte array.
    DoubleBinaryFieldAdapter
    Implements a field adapter for binary, double-precision, floating-point fields.
    FloatBinaryFieldAdapter
    Implements a field adapter for binary, single-precision, floating-point fields.
    IntegerBinaryFieldAdapter
    Implements a field adapter for binary integer fields.
    NumericTextFieldAdapter
    Implements a field adapter for numeric fields stored in textual format, as in a character table.
    TableBinaryAdapter  
    TableCharacterAdapter  
    TableDelimitedAdapter  
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    AdapterFactory
    Implements a factory for getting adapter facade objects.
    DelimiterType
    Defines a set of field and record delimiters for a table.
